ğŸ“˜ Overview

This project implements an end-to-end Engine Health Monitoring System capable of predicting the Remaining Useful Life (RUL) of jet engines. Using the NASA CMAPSS dataset (FD001â€“FD004), the system applies a hybrid CNN + BiLSTM + Attention deep learning architecture to model:

Sensor degradation patterns

Fault progression

Long-range temporal dependencies

The notebook includes preprocessing, sliding-window feature generation, training, checkpointing, and test-set evaluation with PHM Score â€” making it ready for real-world use and ideal for engineering showcases such as Airbus internship applications.

